<D>__{...cause its witchcraft, wicked witchcraft...and although i know its strictly taboo...when you rouse the need in me, my heart says yes indeed in me, proceed with what youre leadin me to...}
<A>__{the camera catches the reactions of guests in the crowd... the women, smiles on their faces, wrapped up in the romance of the moment. envy on the mens faces as they watch jack serenade his wife... a musical interlude from bill as jack takes off his jacket...some hoots and hollers from the crowd...arnie captures the image of kate whistling at her husband... arnie follows with the camera as jack strolls in front of the gathered guests...}
<C>__{jack }
<D>__{its such an ancient pitch, but one that id never switch, there aint no nicer witch than you...}
